Source-level summary
--------------------
In quivilib/control/canvas.py:

    img.preload_animation(block=True)

In quivilib/model/image/freeimage.py:

    def preload_animation(self, block=False):
        ...
        target = self.zoomed_bmp if self.zoomed_bmp else self.img
        target.preload_frames(block)

In pyfreeimage/image.py:

    def preload_frames(self, block=False):
        ...
        if block:
            preload()
            return
        t = threading.Thread(target=preload)
        t.setDaemon(True)
        t.start()

Behavior change
---------------
- Animated playback startup now waits for the currently displayed frame set to
  finish preloading.
- This can add a deliberate short wait before animation starts, especially after
  scaling or fit changes.
- Once playback starts, it should avoid the first-pass frame drops caused by lazy
  scaled-frame creation.
- Existing background preload behavior remains available for callers that do not
  pass block=True.

